285
00:16:26.926 --> 00:16:32.206
Yeah. "The shadows will vanish" means
they'll be enveloped in light.

286
00:16:32.206 --> 00:16:34.856
That light is the moon's light.

287
00:16:34.856 --> 00:16:36.186
It's referring to the "Moonlight Sonata."

288
00:16:36.356 --> 00:16:39.886
That's it. Both 12 years
ago and two years ago,

289
00:16:39.886 --> 00:16:44.726
the "Moonlight Sonata" was playing right
up until Aso-san and Kameyama-san died.

290
00:16:45.206 --> 00:16:48.476
In other words, if the
shadows will vanish again,

291
00:16:48.476 --> 00:16:52.856
that means the "Moonlight Sonata" will be
played again, and somebody else will die.

292
00:16:52.856 --> 00:16:54.316
Wait a minute.

293
00:16:54.676 --> 00:16:57.836
This letter says that the shadows
will "begin to vanish."

294
00:16:59.016 --> 00:17:03.206
Does that mean there's more to this case?

295
00:17:06.646 --> 00:17:07.726
Sheesh.

296
00:17:09.036 --> 00:17:14.576
If you ask me, spending the night
here with the body is insanity.

297
00:17:15.046 --> 00:17:16.856
Well, you know...

298
00:17:17.106 --> 00:17:21.096
More importantly, who moved the body?

299
00:17:21.096 --> 00:17:23.016
That was me.

300
00:17:23.016 --> 00:17:27.176
I felt bad about leaving
him in that position.

301
00:17:27.176 --> 00:17:28.926
You shouldn't have done that.

302
00:17:28.926 --> 00:17:31.196
The crime scene hasn't been
properly examined yet.

303
00:17:31.196 --> 00:17:32.386
Huh?

304
00:17:32.786 --> 00:17:34.786
That sheet music is missing.

305
00:17:34.976 --> 00:17:36.236
What?

306
00:17:36.236 --> 00:17:40.876
Oh, I thought I'd hold
onto it for safekeeping.

307
00:17:40.876 --> 00:17:41.706
Here.

308
00:17:42.746 --> 00:17:46.056
Huh? This is the sheet music
for the "Moonlight Sonata."

309
00:17:46.056 --> 00:17:47.296
Th-The "Moonlight Sonata"?

310
00:17:48.836 --> 00:17:52.576
