311
00:17:52.576 --> 00:17:53.846
The fourth line?

312
00:17:54.456 --> 00:17:56.076
Weird how?

313
00:17:56.076 --> 00:17:57.476
Ready?

314
00:17:58.206 --> 00:18:00.416
When you play the fourth line...

315
00:18:04.606 --> 00:18:05.716
See?

316
00:18:06.366 --> 00:18:12.696
Could the fourth line of this sheet music
be a dying message from Kawashima-san?

317
00:18:13.426 --> 00:18:18.246
Which means it's possible that the
culprit will return to retrieve this.

318
00:18:21.426 --> 00:18:23.246
Doctor Narumi?

319
00:18:23.246 --> 00:18:27.286
I called your inn, and
they said you'd be here.

320
00:18:27.286 --> 00:18:29.756
I brought you dinner.

321
00:18:29.756 --> 00:18:31.826
N-Now that you mention it...

322
00:18:34.866 --> 00:18:35.996
Really?

323
00:18:36.256 --> 00:18:39.956
So you're not originally from
this island, Doctor Narumi?

324
00:18:39.956 --> 00:18:43.756
No. I go back to Tokyo every weekend.

325
00:18:44.036 --> 00:18:47.006
It's been two years since
I started coming here.

326
00:18:47.006 --> 00:18:48.706
Speaking of two years,

327
00:18:48.706 --> 00:18:51.386
I have a question about Mayor
Kameyama who died two years ago.

328
00:18:51.656 --> 00:18:57.626
He'd previously had heart problems, and
the cause of death was a heart attack.

329
00:18:58.006 --> 00:19:01.286
But his face was rather tense,

330
00:19:01.846 --> 00:19:05.036
as though he'd seen something terrifying.

331
00:19:05.406 --> 00:19:08.956
He looked like he'd seen
something terrifying, huh?

332
00:19:11.836 --> 00:19:16.036
In any case, I'll keep watch tonight.

333
